Roles & Responsibilities
Job Summary
An exciting opportunity to be an IT Business Analyst to coordinate with various stakeholders and work on business process improvement through IT.

Mandatory Skill-set
Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science or equivalent;
At least 1 - 3 years of experience in managing IT applications;
Proven experience in gathering business requirements and translating them into functional and technical specifications;
Curious in understanding business requirements thoroughly and analyze them to come up with specifications to be developed by the technical team;
Strong stakeholders management skills to manage both business users' expectation and technical team's capability in delivering the solutions;
Detail oriented to manage requirements precisely;
Self motivated with high sense of ownership;
Great written and spoken communication skills.
Desired Skill-set
ITIL, CBAP and/or PMP certified.
Responsibilities
Design and rollout business process improvement initiatives through IT;
Gather and analyze requirements from users, and write functional & technical specifications;
Assist in SIT, UAT and other tests;
Develop documentation / user manual and perform users training;
Design and document application enhancements based on the requirements;
Responsible for providing daily support of applications to ensure that they are up and running;
Involve in project management such as planning, costing, scheduling, resource management, vendor management, risk management and reporting.
Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest.

